subset_coe_pow:
theorem subset_coe_pow (p : sub_mul_action R M) : ∀ {n : ℕ}, (p ^ n : set M) ⊆ ↑(p ^ n)
  | 0 => by
    rw [pow_zero, pow_zero]
    exact subset_coe_one
  | n + 1 => (coe_pow p n.succ_ne_zero).superset
#align subset_coe_pow subset_coe_pow
subset_coe_one:
theorem subset_coe_one : (1 : set M) ⊆ (1 : sub_mul_action R M) := fun x hx => ⟨1, (one_smul _ _).trans hx.symm⟩
#align subset_coe_one subset_coe_one
mem_one:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr • » -/
@[simp]
theorem mem_one {x : M} : x ∈ (1 : sub_mul_action R M) ↔ ∃ r : R, «expr • » r 1 = x :=
  iff.rfl
#align mem_one mem_one
mem_mul:
theorem mem_mul {p q : sub_mul_action R M} {x : M} : x ∈ p * q ↔ ∃ y z, y ∈ p ∧ z ∈ q ∧ y * z = x :=
  Set.mem_mul
#align mem_mul mem_mul
coe_pow:
theorem coe_pow (p : sub_mul_action R M) : ∀ {n : ℕ} (hn : n ≠ 0), ↑(p ^ n) = (p ^ n : set M)
  | 0, hn => (hn rfl).elim
  | 1, hn => by rw [pow_one, pow_one]
  | n + 2, hn => by rw [pow_succ _ (n + 1), pow_succ _ (n + 1), coe_mul, coe_pow n.succ_ne_zero]
#align coe_pow coe_pow
coe_one:

theorem coe_one : ↑(1 : sub_mul_action R M) = Set.range fun r : R => «expr • » r (1 : M) :=
  rfl
#align coe_one coe_one
coe_mul:
@[norm_cast]
theorem coe_mul (p q : sub_mul_action R M) : ↑(p * q) = (p * q : set M) :=
  rfl
#align coe_mul coe_mul
